      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and<strong> grated garlic </strong>with<strong> </strong>60ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[90ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[120ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong>,<strong> </strong>your <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>and<strong> chicken stock mix</strong> – this is your <strong>mustard sauce</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>mustard sauce</strong> to the pan, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook for 4-5 min further or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>creamy mustard chicken</strong></p><p>Tip: If it looks a little dry, add a splash of water!</p>",
